modules.title: What is DeFi or Decentralized Finance

image.title: What is DeFi or Decentralized Finance

childMarkdownRemark.html:
DeFi—decentralized finance—refers to peer-to-peer finance enabled by decentralized technologies built on the Ethereum blockchain. It is a shift from traditional, centralized financial systems to open accessible platforms available to all instead of a select few.

With MetaMask you can step into this global financial ecosystem easily to swap, stake, and earn yield on your tokens.

Swapping tokens is easy and safe with MetaMask. Utilizing data from decentralized exchanges and market makers is aggregated within the wallet for you to get the best prices.

Learn more about how MetaMask makes swapping easier here.

You can buy crypto directly within MetaMask. With over 175 countries supported, Metamask’s aggregation welcomes users globally to Web3. The enhanced experience will present you the best quotes to fund your wallet based on your region, payment provider, and token you select.

Learn more about buying crypto without leaving the app here.

Staking allows you to deposit your tokens for financial rewards. Similar to how an interest-bearing financial account works, stakers receive interest for helping to ensure the state of the Ethereum network.
